{
  "word": "adjacent",
  "wordRoot": [
    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#5117\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">adjacent</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>15世纪初，“相邻的，毗邻的； 近的”，源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacentem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacens</span>）“位于”， <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacere</span> 的现在分词，“位于，毗邻，靠近”，由 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad</span> “到”（见 <a href=\"/cn/word/ad-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">ad-</a>)和 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">iacēre</span> “躺，休息”组成，与 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">iacere</span> “扔； 放”有关（来自 PIE 根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*ye-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *ye- \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*ye-</a> “扔，推动”）。仅用于事物，从不用于人或动物。 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">Adjacent</span>，正确来说，是指附近但不一定接触； <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">adjoining</span> 是指接触。拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacentia</span> 的意思是“邻近”。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "adagio<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adv.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>大约1746年，用于音乐领域，意为“缓慢、从容、优美”，源自意大利语，是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad agio</i> 的缩写，由 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">ad</i> “在、于”（参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of ad- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/ad-\">ad-</a>)和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">agio</i> “闲暇”组成，源自通俗拉丁语* <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacens</i>，是 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">adiacere</i> “躺在、靠近”的现在分词形式（类似于 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of adjacent \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/adjacent\">adjacent</a>）。名词意义上的“缓慢的动作”首次出现于1784年。</p>"
    },
    {
      "title": "coadjacent<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(adj.)</div>",
      "html": "<p>同时也有 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">co-adjacent</i>，意为“相互相邻”，始见于1842年，由 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of co- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/co-\">co-</a> 和 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of adjacent \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/adjacent\">adjacent</a> 组成。相关词汇： <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">Coadjacence</i>。</p>"
    }
  ]
}